# Support-bundle delivery credentials — LOCAL TESTING template.
#
# Copy this file to `support-secrets.local` (gitignored by the repo's `*.local`
# rule) and fill in real values, then rebuild. The build script (build.rs)
# reads it and injects the values at compile time via `cargo:rustc-env`, so
# `option_env!("SUPPORT_BOT_TOKEN")` / `option_env!("SUPPORT_CHAT_ID")` pick
# them up — no runtime configuration is needed.
#
# CI / release builds do NOT use this file. They set the same two variables as
# environment secrets on the `cargo tauri build` step
# (see .github/workflows/build.yml), and build.rs prefers the real environment
# over this file so a stale local copy can never shadow CI.
#
# How to get the values:
#   SUPPORT_BOT_TOKEN  — the full token from @BotFather for the
#                        HomeEnergyManagerSupportBot (looks like
#                        `123456789:AAExx...`). Not just the numeric bot id.
#   SUPPORT_CHAT_ID    — where submissions should land: your personal chat id
#                        (message @userinfobot to get yours), a private channel
#                        (`@channelname` or `-100...`), or a group id. The bot
#                        must be a member/admin of the destination.
#
# Format: one KEY=VALUE per line. Lines starting with `#` are ignored.

SUPPORT_BOT_TOKEN=123456789:AAExxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
SUPPORT_CHAT_ID=999999999
